article.headline: Alabama 87, Oregon 86
article.story: LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Kennedy Winston scored 27 points and made a jumper with 4.5 seconds left to lift Alabama past Oregon 87-86 Saturday at the Las Vegas Showdown. Oregon's Luke Jackson nearly won the game for the Ducks at the buzzer, but his running shot rimmed in and out. A 3-pointer from Andre Joseph with 1:01 left gave Oregon an 86-83 lead in a game that featured nine ties and 13 lead changes. But a Chuck Davis dunk and a defensive stop set the table for Winston's heroics. Earnest Shelton had 16 points for Alabama, Antoine Pettaway had 12 and Thomas Emmett and Davis had 11 apiece. Alabama (6-2) led 54-46 at the half, but Oregon (4-2) hit six second-half 3-pointers and quickly erased the deficit. The Ducks went on a 13-6 run over the first four minutes of the second half and trailed 61-59. Ian Crosswhite led Oregon with 21 points and eight rebounds. Joseph had 17 and Jackson added 15 for the Ducks. Alabama shot 58 percent in the first half, highlighted by back-to-back 3-pointers from Emmett Thomas to take an 18-16 lead at the 12:52 mark. Winston had 17 points on 7-of-10 shooting in the first half.
